The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Tata Tea Arsenal soccer stars training camp started at the CC amp;FC grounds on Tuesday, where 30 under-15 colts will receive training under Arsenal coaches Paul Shipwright and Martin Davis. The boys will be tutored in two sessions till June 11. At the end of the camp, 15 will be shortlisted and given the opportunity to attend coaching at Arsenal.          
	 Sougata Sarkar and Anindita Chakraborty clinched the mens singles and womens singles titles, respectively, in the Kalyan Jayant Table Tennis Championship held at Bijoynagar club in Naihati. Sandip Pal won the sub-junior boys singles title and the sub-junior girls singles title went to Camelia Sil. Anirban Sinha Roy won the junior boys title and Kirtika Sinha Roy won the junior girls singles event.                                                                                                                                                                      
